issue_body:
I am not sure if this issue is platform-related or due to the poor C++11 support by MSVC (Windows 7 + VS2015, Dlib version 19.4)
Would you please advise the possible root cause? Thank you in advance.

```C++
#include <dlib/image_processing.h>
#include <dlib/image_transforms.h>
#include <dlib/opencv.h>

using namespace dlib;

cv::Mat getFaceChipImage(cv::Mat src_img, unsigned long size, double padding) const {
	cv_image<array2d<rgb_pixel>> dlib_cvimg(src_img);     // <<<< Apparent
	cv_image<array2d<rgb_pixel>> face_chip;
	extract_image_chip(dlib_cvimg, get_face_chip_details(shape, size, padding), face_chip);
	cv::Mat mat = toMat(face_chip);
	return mat;
}
```

Compilation of above function encountered the following errors in `dlib\include\dlib\opencv\cv_image.h`:
```C++
line 28:
- Error C2027:	use of undefined type 'dlib::pixel_traits<pixel_type>'	
- Error C2146:	syntax error: missing '>' before identifier 'basic_pixel_type' 
- Error C2065:	'num': undeclared identifier 
```

```C++
line 36:
- Error C2027:	use of undefined type 'dlib::pixel_traits<pixel_type>'
- Error C2146:	syntax error: missing '>' before identifier 'basic_pixel_type'
- Error C2065:	'num': undeclared identifier
```

