>If you wish to group certain switches together in the help message, you can specify group = "Group Name", where Group Name is any string.

>COLOR_GROUPS = {"Meta-switches" : colors.bold & colors.yellow}

It can be a bit inconvenient and looks a bit ugly. Should we encapsulate all these in ```Group``` class?

I need to use two `use_kwargs` on one view function with location `json` and `headers`:
```
class HeaderSchema(Schema):
    header_field = fields.String()


class BodySchema(Schema):
    body_field = fields.String()


@use_kwargs(HeaderSchema, locations=['headers'])
@use_kwargs(BodySchema, locations=['json'])
def get(self, **kwargs):
    ...
```

However, in the generate swagger spec JSON, only the outer `@use_kwargs` gets parsed (in the above case, `HeaderSchema`. It seems that the outer `kwargs` overrides the inner one.

Is there a way to go around this issue?

