# Issue Title

MultipartReader Instance Method (ReadNextSectionAsync) throws IOException: Unexpected end of Stream, the content may have already been read by another component.

# General

I wrote a Custom media formatter for a WEB API project running on .NET core 2.0 Windows 10 (64 bit). On the ReadRequestBodyAsync method I was accessing the content body and on using reader=MultipartReader(boundary, context.HttpContext.Request.Body)
reader.readNextSectionAsync() this error with stack trace below occured

at Microsoft.AspNetCore.WebUtilities.MultipartReaderStream.d__36.MoveNext() 
--- End of stack trace from previous location where exception was thrown --- at System.Runtime.ExceptionServices.ExceptionDispatchInfo.Throw() at System.Runtime.CompilerServices.TaskAwaiter.HandleNonSuccessAndDebuggerNotification(Task task) at Microsoft.AspNetCore.WebUtilities.StreamHelperExtensions.d__3.MoveNext() 
--- End of stack trace from previous location where exception was thrown --- at System.Runtime.ExceptionServices.ExceptionDispatchInfo.Throw() at System.Runtime.CompilerServices.TaskAwaiter.HandleNonSuccessAndDebuggerNotification(Task task) at Microsoft.AspNetCore.WebUtilities.MultipartReader.d__20.MoveNext() 
--- End of stack trace from previous location where exception was thrown --- at System.Runtime.ExceptionServices.ExceptionDispatchInfo.Throw() at System.Runtime.CompilerServices.TaskAwaiter.HandleNonSuccessAndDebuggerNotification(Task task) at System.Runtime.CompilerServices.TaskAwaiter`1.GetResult() at Quizac.Data.API.Models.RequestFormatter`1.d__2.MoveNext() in C:\Users\user\Documents\Visual Studio 2017\Projects\*********\Models\Utilities.cs:line 137

 public async override Task<InputFormatterResult> ReadRequestBodyAsync(InputFormatterContext context)
        {
            var requestContentType = context.HttpContext.Request.ContentType.ToLower();
            var isMultipartContentType = !string.IsNullOrEmpty(requestContentType) && requestContentType.Contains("multipart/");
            var provider = context.HttpContext.Request.Body;
            var contentLength = context.HttpContext.Request.ContentLength;
            long TotalBytes = contentLength.HasValue && contentLength.Value > 0 ? contentLength.Value : 0;

            var requestContentTypeElements = requestContentType.Split(' ');
            var boundaryElement = requestContentTypeElements.Where(el => el.StartsWith("boundary=")).First();
            var boundary = boundaryElement.Substring("boundary=".Length).Trim('"');
            if (string.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(boundary))
            {
                throw new Exception("Boundary missing.");
            }
            //mthv.Boundary.Value.ToLower()
            boundary = "";
            MediaTypeHeaderValue mthv = MediaTypeHeaderValue.Parse(context.HttpContext.Request.ContentType);
            MultipartReader reader = new MultipartReader(boundary, context.HttpContext.Request.Body);

            var instance = Activator.CreateInstance(typeof(T));
            MultipartSection section = null;
            var properties = typeof(T).GetProperties();
            try
            {
                var read = await reader.ReadNextSectionAsync();
            }
            catch (Exception ex)
            {

                throw;
            }
          
            while ((section = await reader.ReadNextSectionAsync()) != null)
            {
                var property = properties.FirstOrDefault(p => section.ContentDisposition.TrimQuotation().ToLower() == p.Name.ToLower());
                if (property.PropertyType == typeof(String))
                {
                    string data = await section.ReadAsStringAsync();
                    property.SetValue(instance, data);
                }

                else
                    if (property.PropertyType == typeof(double) || property.PropertyType == typeof(int) || property.PropertyType == typeof(int?) || property.PropertyType == typeof(decimal?) || property.PropertyType == typeof(bool?) || property.PropertyType == typeof(long?))
                { 
                    string data = await section.ReadAsStringAsync();
                    if (property.PropertyType == typeof(int))
                        property.SetValue(instance, int.Parse(data));

                    if ((property.PropertyType == typeof(double)))
                        property.SetValue(instance, double.Parse(data));

                    if ((property.PropertyType == typeof(int?)))
                    {
                        int val;
                        property.SetValue(instance, int.TryParse(data, out val) ? val : (int?)null);
                    }

                    if ((property.PropertyType == typeof(decimal?)))
                    {
                        decimal val;
                        property.SetValue(instance, decimal.TryParse(data, out val) ? val : (decimal?)null);
                    }

                    if ((property.PropertyType == typeof(bool?)))
                    {
                        bool val;
                        property.SetValue(instance, bool.TryParse(data, out val) ? val : (bool?)null);
                    }

                    if ((property.PropertyType == typeof(long?)))
                    {
                        long val;
                        property.SetValue(instance, long.TryParse(data, out val) ? val : (long?)null);
                    }

                }


                else if (property.PropertyType == typeof(File))
                {
                    File file = new File();
                    file.Data = new byte[section.AsFileSection().FileStream.Length];
                    await section.AsFileSection().FileStream.ReadAsync(file.Data, 0, file.Data.Length);
                    file.Name = section.ContentDisposition.TrimQuotation();
                    file.MimeType = section.ContentType.Trim().ToLower();
                    property.SetValue(instance, file);
                }

                else if (property.PropertyType is IList<File> && section.ContentType.IsMultipartFormData())
                {
                    MultipartReader multipartFilesReader = new MultipartReader(MediaTypeHeaderValue.Parse(section.ContentType).Boundary.Value, context.HttpContext.Request.Body);
                    List<File> fileList = new List<File>();
                    MultipartSection fileSection = null;
                    while ((fileSection = await multipartFilesReader.ReadNextSectionAsync()) != null)
                    {
                        File file = new File();
                        file.Data = new byte[section.AsFileSection().FileStream.Length];
                        await section.AsFileSection().FileStream.ReadAsync(file.Data, 0, file.Data.Length);
                        file.MimeType = section.ContentType;
                        fileList.Add(file);
                    }
                    property.SetValue(instance, fileList);

                }
                else if (property.PropertyType is Object && section.ContentType != null)
                {
                    if (section.ContentType.IsJson())
                    {
                        try
                        {
                            string objString = await section.ReadAsStringAsync();
                            var obj = JsonConvert.DeserializeObject(objString, property.PropertyType);
                            property.SetValue(instance, obj);


                        }
                        catch (Exception ex)
                        {

                        }

                    }
                    else if (section.ContentType.IsMultipartFormData())
                    {
                        // property.SetValue(instance, ReadRequestBodyAsync(section));
                    }
                }

            }

            return InputFormatterResult.Success(instance);
        }

I use [hashids](http://hashids.org/) to encode ID values when serializing objects. The most straightforward way to doing this seemed to me to declare ID field using `fields.Method`. However when serializing a `Relationship` field then it picks up ID value straight from the source object instead of obtaining it through the schema`s ID field.

Example code:

```python
from marshmallow import pprint
from marshmallow_jsonapi import Schema, fields

class BaseSchema(Schema):
    id = fields.Method('serialize_id', dump_only=True)

    def serialize_id(self, obj):
        # faking hashids.encode()
        return "%s+%s"%(self.opts.type_, obj['id'])

class CarSchema(BaseSchema):
    class Meta:
        type_ = 'cars'
        self_url = '/cars/{id}'
        self_url_kwargs = { 'id': '<id>' }

    name = fields.Str()
    parts = fields.Relationship(
        many=True,
        self_url='/cars/{id}/parts',
        self_url_kwargs={'id': '<id>'},
        include_resource_linkage=True,
        type_="parts",
        schema="PartSchema",
        required=True)

class PartSchema(BaseSchema):
    class Meta:
        type_ = 'parts'
        self_url = '/parts/{id}'
        self_url_kwargs = { 'id': '<id>' }

    name = fields.Str()

data = {
    'id': '0',
    'name': 'tesla',
    'parts': [
        {'id': '10', 'name': 'battery'}
    ]
}

pprint(CarSchema().dump(data).data)

{'attributes': {'name': 'tesla'},
 'id': 'cars+0',
 'links': {'self': '/cars/cars+0'},
 'relationships': {'parts': {'data': [{'id': '10', 'type': 'parts'}],
                             'links': {'self': '/cars/0/parts'}}},
 'type': 'cars'}
```

I would expect that `relationships.parts.links.self` should equal to `/cars/cars+0` and the related part ID `10` should equal to `parts+10` since `schema` is specified on the `parts` relationship field. Or is this an expected serialization behavior?

